<TITLE> Saifur's son faces arrest for graft </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 3(bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court on Monday ordered arrest of former finance minister Saifur Rahman's son Mohammad Shafiur Babu on charge of acquiring illegal wealth and concealing information. Dhaka Metropolitan Senior Special Judge Mohammad Azizul Haque issued the warrant of arrest. On Sunday, Mohammad Farid Ahmed Patoari, assistant director of Anticorruption Commission (ACC), presses the chargesheet with the court against Babu. The chargesheet stated Babu had earned illegal properties worth around Tk 1.3 crore. He had also covered up information of wealth worth 1.22 crore in the assets statement submitted to the ACC. ACC's deputy assistant director Sharmeen Ferdausi filed a case against Babu on April 29 this year. bdnew
